### Setting Up Simulation

1. In Vivado **Sources** panel, expand **Simulation Sources** → **sim_1**
2. Right-click [TopLevelProcessor_tb.v](file:///c:/Users/ba09716/Downloads/labProjectCA/labProjectCA.srcs/sim_1/new/TopLevelProcessor_tb.v) → **Set as Top**
3. Make sure the design sources have [TopLevelProcessor.v](file:///c:/Users/ba09716/Downloads/labProjectCA/labProjectCA.srcs/sources_1/new/TopLevelProcessor.v) as the synthesis top (not TopLevelFPGA for simulation)

### Running Simulation

1. Click **Flow Navigator** → **Simulation** → **Run Behavioral Simulation**
2. The simulation runs for ~650 ns and auto-finishes
3. Check the **Tcl Console** at the bottom for text output:

```
=== Task B Test Program Started ===
No switches needed - program is self-running.

--- After LUI test (rom[0]-rom[3]) ---
  display_out = 0x00005003 (expect 0x00005003 if LUI+ADDI worked)
  >> LUI TEST PASSED <<
```

### What Waveforms to Look For

Add these signals to the waveform viewer (right-click → Add to Wave Window):

| Signal | Path | What to watch |
|--------|------|---------------|
| `clk` | `uut/clk` | Clock reference |
| `rst` | `uut/rst` | Goes low at 100 ns |
| `PC` | `uut/PC` | Should increment by 4 each cycle |
| `instruction` | `uut/instruction` | The fetched instruction hex |
| `ALUResult` | `uut/ALUResult` | ALU output value |
| `display_out` | `uut/display_out` | What gets shown on LEDs/7-seg |
| `Zero` | `uut/Zero` | ALU zero flag |
| `Less_Than` | `uut/Less_Than` | ALU less-than flag (for BLT) |
| `branch_taken` | `uut/branch_taken` | Whether branch fires |

